history.content: No more reserved seating for EECS but if you waitlist yourself it looks likely that you'll get in judging by the current enrolled/waitlisted numbers

The student is correct that the reserved seats were already released (see @543) and that there are currently enough seats left in the class to clear the waitlist. Please note you will only be automatically enrolled off the waitlist if you choose secondary sections with open seats. Choosing sections with only a few open seats is not recommended as they may fill by the time you are reached. 

You should confirm there will be an alternate final exam time with the EE16A faculty (see @447 and @464).

I enrolled in Physics 7A because I had a final conflict between EE16A and another class, however I really want to take EE16A this Spring because I just took Math 54 and many of the concepts are similar. I heard that there will be an alternate final exam time for EE16A, so I want to drop Physics 7A and enroll in EE16A now, but I'm not sure if I have a seat reserved at this point as an EECS freshman and I don't want to lose my spot in Physics 7A. 

Is there any way for me to get into 16A at this point? Any help is appreciated!
history.subject: EE16A — Spots still reserved for an EECS freshman?
